You need to understand is why the bottom didn&#39;t immediately drop. It didn&#39;t drop for the same reason that it didn&#39;t drop when the guy was holding the other end; the tension force (upwards) counters the gravity (downwards). When the tension drops, gravity takes over. There is a delay before the tension change is transferred down.

If you generate tension forever, the bottom will obviously &quot;hover&quot; forever. This could be done, for example, by attaching the top of the slinky somewhere.
